I"u∫<p>Once Jekyll is running, you can start with basic configuration by adding various entries to <code class="highlighter-rouge">_config.yml</code>.
Besides these descriptions, you can also read the <a href="#annotated-config-file">annotated config file</a> below.</p>

<p class="message"><strong>NOTE</strong>: When making changes to <code class="highlighter-rouge">_config.yml</code>, it is necessary to restart the Jekyll process for the changes to take effect.</p>

